//START - .ENV.EXAMPLE
# ==============================================================================
# L33tOS Database Configuration - EXAMPLE FILE
# ==============================================================================
# 
# ⚠️  WARNING: INSECURE DEFAULTS FOR DEVELOPMENT ONLY!
# 
# These are intentionally insecure defaults for local development.
# DO NOT USE THESE SETTINGS IN PRODUCTION!
# 
# For production:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (not tracked by git)
# 2. Update all credentials with strong, unique values
# 3. Ensure .env is listed in .gitignore
# 4. Use a dedicated database user with minimal privileges
# ==============================================================================

# Database Host (default: localhost)
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1

# Database Name
DB_NAME=l33tos

# Database User (⚠️  CHANGE IN PRODUCTION!)
DB_USER=root

# Database Password (⚠️  BLANK IS INSECURE - SET A STRONG PASSWORD!)
DB_PASS=

# ==============================================================================
# PRODUCTION CHECKLIST:
# - [ ] Create strong DB_PASS
# - [ ] Create dedicated database user (not root)
# - [ ] Grant only required privileges
# - [ ] Verify .env is in .gitignore
# - [ ] Never commit .env to version control
# ==============================================================================
//END - .ENV.EXAMPLE
